ame <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip de Stackpole I was born about 1210, in Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales, his father, Robert de Stackpole, was 57 and his mother, Sitsyll, was 53. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1280, in his hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"Abt 1210–1280":"umbes 1210–1280","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1230–1298":"1230–1298","1155–1219":"1155–1219","1159–Female":"1159–Surnud","1159":"1159","1324":"1324","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1155":"1155","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1219":"1219","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"Abt 1210–1280":"noin 1210–1280","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1230–1298":"1230–1298","1155–1219":"1155–1219","1159–Female":"1159–Kuollut","1159":"1159","1324":"1324","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","1155":"1155","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1219":"1219","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"Abt 1210–1280":"environ 1210–1280","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1230–1298":"1230–1298","1155–1219":"1155–1219","1159–Female":"1159–Décédée","1159":"1159","1324":"1324","Abt 1210":"environ 1210","1155":"1155","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1219":"1219","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Philip de Stackpole I est né environ 1210, à Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Galles, son père, Robert de Stackpole, avait 57 ans et sa mère, Sitsyll, avait 53 ans. Il a eu au moins